[3] Los Angeles county
Date: Sat 22 Jun 2019 2:08 PM PDT
Source: NBC Los Angeles, City News Service [abridged, edited]
https://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/local/Two-New-Measles-Cases-Connected-To-West-LA-511679621.html


Los Angeles county health officials said [Sat 22 Jun 2019] that they are looking into identifying anyone who may have been exposed to 2 residents who recently traveled and became ill with measles shortly after returning to the county.

These 2 new cases were not linked to each other and were likely exposed to measles while traveling outside of the United States.

There have been 10 measles cases among Los Angeles county residents in 2019, in addition to 8 non-resident measles cases that traveled through Los Angeles county. Of the 10 measles cases among residents, 5 are not linked to any of the others, and 3 of these cases are linked to international travel.

The majority of the cases were unvaccinated, officials said.

[See source URL above for locations of exposure. - Mod.MK]

