[9] Madagascar
Date: Mon 24 Jun 2019
Source: BBC News, Focus on Africa [edited]
https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p07dkjhw


Understaffed health facilities and bad roads are only a few of the challenges of vaccinating against measles in Madagascar. Listen as the BBC's Pumza Fihlani travels to a remote village and speaks to the health workers carrying out the vaccinations and the people who often have to travel far to get immunised. Poverty, malnutrition, bringing in vaccine, all contribute to the problem.

